Interface TerminalConflictResolution<I,​O>

    Functional Interface:

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface TerminalConflictResolution<I,​O>
extends ConflictResolution<I,​O>
    A conflict resolution function that is guaranteed to produce a single value.

    For example, a resolution may simply retain all values in a list and thus will always resolve the conflict.

        Description copied from interface: ConflictResolution
        Tries the best to resolve the value but may end up with multiple concurrent values.

        For example, if two values "a" and "b" with equal weight remain after prior resolution, this method returns a list of both.

        The return value should be treated as a bag; that is, the order of the values does not matter.

        Specified by:
        resolveNonEmptyPartially in interface ConflictResolution<I,​O>
        Parameters:

        context - a fusion context with additional configurations.
        Returns:
